Rion:

Rion fluttered wildly as he tried to slow down. He looked back, just in time 
to see Diana wailing for him to stop before turning to face te monster. He 
wasn't about to abandon her. Nuh-uh.

"Hang on! I'm coming!"

Rion pulled to the side as he did a quick u-turn in mid-air and flew at top 
speed to Diana's side. He landed beside her, skidding to a stop just inches 
before the monster.

"Yikes!"

Rion jumped back. That was a little 'too' close for comfort. He drew his 
sword and gulped loudly. His knees were shaking but he wasn't about to leave 
Diana alone with this thing.

*****

Hysteria had made her way through the ship, repairing what little damage she 
could. Most of it was either not worth the effort or out of her limited 
reach. She was of something at a loss when it came to high places. Still, 
she did her best.

(I'm not exactly sure what's going on with the CF right now, so I'll keep
